@startuml elastic_network_capacity
!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/behavioral/activity-diagram-style.iuml

title Elastic Network Capacity Architecture\nDynamic allocation of bandwidth and ports to avoid runtime bottlenecks

|Cloud Consumer|
start
:Send requests to cloud service;

|Automated Scaling Listener|
:Monitor workload and
network traffic;
if (Bandwidth threshold reached?) then (yes)
  :Signal intelligent automation engine;
else (no)
  :Continue monitoring;
  stop
endif

|Intelligent Automation Engine|
if (Implemented at virtual switch level?) then (yes)
  :Run script to add
  physical uplinks
  to virtual switch;
else (no)
  :Allocate additional bandwidth
  and/or network ports
  from network resource pool;
endif

|Network Resource Pool|
:Provide shared
network ports
(isolated per consumer);

|Cloud Consumer|
:Traffic flows through
expanded capacity;
stop

note right
  Each cloud consumer uses a
  different set of network ports
  to isolate individual traffic flows.

  Direct I/O Access architecture
  may also be incorporated to
  raise virtual server bandwidth.
end note

note left
  Supporting mechanisms:
  Cloud Usage Monitor, Hypervisor,
  Logical Network Perimeter,
  Pay-Per-Use Monitor,
  Resource Replication, Virtual Server
end note

@enduml

